Here's a code snippet using Python and Matplotlib to generate this chart:

```python
import json
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the data
with open('./db/new_data.json') as f:
    data = json.load(f)

# Prepare the data for the chart
departments = [job["department"] for job in data["jobs"]]
job_counts = {department: departments.count(department) for department in set(departments)}

# Generate the chart
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(job_counts.keys(), job_counts.values(), color='skyblue')
plt.title('Number of Jobs per Department')
plt.xlabel('Department')
plt.ylabel('Number of Jobs')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Display the chart
plt.show()
```

